## 🔄 Deployment Steps Summary

### Phase 1: Server Preparation
1. ✅ Install Windows Server 2012
2. ✅ Configure network settings
3. ✅ Apply security updates
4. ✅ Create administrator account

### Phase 2: IIS Installation
1. ✅ Enable Web Server role
2. ✅ Install IIS management tools
3. ✅ Configure default settings
4. ✅ Verify installation

### Phase 3: Application Deployment
1. ✅ Create application directory
2. ✅ Copy application files
3. ✅ Set file permissions
4. ✅ Configure IIS application

### Phase 4: Testing & Optimization
1. ✅ Local functionality testing
2. ✅ Remote access verification
3. ✅ Performance optimization
4. ✅ Security configuration

## ✅ Testing & Verification

### Functional Tests
- [ ] Website loads without errors
- [ ] All navigation links work correctly
- [ ] Course sections display properly
- [ ] Contact information is visible
- [ ] Responsive design works on mobile

### Technical Tests
- [ ] HTTP status codes return 200 OK
- [ ] CSS and JavaScript files load correctly
- [ ] No console errors in browser
- [ ] Server logs show no critical errors
- [ ] Performance is acceptable

### Accessibility Tests
